## What This Module Does

This module provides a robust, low-latency inter-process and inter-node communication system using ZeroMQ. It allows multiple VJLive3 instances or external tools to coordinate state, synchronize clocks, and pass high-frequency telemetry/events (e.g., beat triggers, parameter changes, node graph updates) without blocking the rendering thread. It implements an architecture where nodes can discover each other and subscribe to relevant topics.

---

## What It Does NOT Do

- It does not replace the WebSocket interface used for web UI communication (that serves a different purpose).
- It does not stream large bulk data like video frames (NDI is used for video, P2-H4).
- It does not dictate the contents of the payload, it only provides the transport and routing mechanism.

